## SPEAKER NOTES & TIMING

### Full Presentation (30 Minutes)

**Slide 1 (Title) - 1 min:**
"Hi everyone. I'm Aaron, founder of HDIM. We help health plans close care gaps before HEDIS deadlines using predictive AI. We're raising $750K to scale, and we're on track to do $500K-$1M ARR by end of 2026."

**Slide 2 (Problem) - 4 min:**
"Let me start with the problem we're solving. Health plans leave $500K-$1M on the table every year. Why? Because they identify care gaps too late to close them.

Here's the current workflow [walk through Week 1-6]. By the time gaps are identified, there's only 3 weeks left before the HEDIS deadline. That's not enough time to close complex gaps—providers need 7-14 days just to respond.

The result is 60% gap closure rate. But leading plans are hitting 85%. So the opportunity is clear: identify gaps 30-60 days earlier, and you can close 25% more.

Three pain points: late identification, provider disengagement, and no financial visibility. This affects CMOs, coordinators, CFOs, and providers."

**Slide 3 (Market) - 3 min:**
"The market opportunity is substantial. We're targeting $4.2B serviceable market—800+ health plans in the US, each with $3-5M annual quality bonus pool.

Our beachhead market: primary care health plans. Total addressable market is $12.4B including health systems and ACOs.

Why now? ECDS transition in 2030 means digital-only HEDIS measures. Star ratings are getting harder to hit. Value-based care is 50% of Medicare. Providers are burned out on generic alerts. There's regulatory tailwind and competitive opportunity."

**Slide 4 (Solution) - 4 min:**
"We solve this three ways. First, predictive gap detection. Instead of waiting for historical data, we use AI to predict gaps 30-60 days ahead. We analyzed 12 health plans—those using prediction hit 85% gap closure vs. 60% industry average. That's 35-40% improvement.

Second, AI clinical narratives. Generic gap lists get 5-10% provider response. Our AI-powered narratives [show example] get 50%+ response because providers understand WHY the gap matters. This is 3x higher engagement, and coordinators love it.

Third, real-time financial ROI tracking. This is Phase 3—a dashboard showing exactly how many quality bonuses were captured, broken down by measure. No legacy vendor offers this. CMOs can finally prove value to CFOs."

**Slide 5 (Traction) - 3 min:**
"We've validated this with 5 health plans. In 15 discovery interviews, we found consistent pain points—the timing gap is THE issue, provider engagement is broken, and financial visibility is missing.

Product-wise, we have MVP deployed. 2 reference customers are using it. We're hitting 88% prediction accuracy, 99.9% uptime, and 2-4 week implementations.

Right now we're executing Phase 2. Starting March 1, we're running 50-100 discovery calls with a new VP Sales. We're targeting 2-3 pilots in April and $50-100K committed revenue by month-end. HEDIS season is our window—urgency is highest, and we deploy in 2-4 weeks vs. competitors' 8-12 weeks."

**Slide 6 (Team & GTM) - 3 min:**
"I bring founder-market fit—I've lived this problem, built the product, validated the market. Our engineering team is solid: HIPAA-certified, 51+ microservices, production-ready.

Over the next 12 months, we'll scale to 20-25 people: VP Sales, AEs, customer success, product, ops.

Our go-to-market is persona-specific. We don't use generic sales pitches. CMOs respond to predictive gap detection. CFOs respond to financial ROI. Coordinators want time savings. Providers want clinical context. IT wants speed and compliance.

We tested this with customers. 15/15 were interested in our approach. We measured 15-25% conversion from discovery to pilot, which is strong for enterprise healthcare."

**Slide 7 (Business Model) - 3 min:**
"The unit economics are venture-fundable. Pilots are $25-50K. Full contracts are $100-300K annually with 75%+ margins.

Customer acquisition cost is $15-25K. Average annual contract value is $100-150K. That's 5-7x LTV/CAC, which is great. Payback period is 2-3 months.

We're conservative on projections. Year 1: $500K-$1M ARR with 1-2 pilots. Year 2: $1-2M with 10-15 customers. Year 3: $2-5M with 30-50 customers.

Monthly burn with this seed round is $85K. That gives us 8-9 months runway, extending to December 2026. By then we should be at $300-500K ARR and have Series A momentum. We can reach break-even by Q2 2027 if we hit targets."

**Slide 8 (Competition) - 2 min:**
"Our competitive advantages are clear. We're 4-6x faster than legacy vendors. More accurate AI. 3x better provider engagement.

More importantly, we have sustainable moats. Clinical narrative AI is hard to replicate—it requires healthcare domain expertise plus LLM expertise. FHIR-native architecture positions us for the 2030 ECDS transition. Customer relationships and data create a moat that grows over time.

If OptumInsight tries to copy, they're locked in legacy architecture. If a new startup competes, we have first-mover advantage and customer relationships. If a health plan builds in-house, they're spending $500K-$2M and 12+ months."

**Slide 9 (Ask) - 2 min:**
"We're raising $750K at a $6M pre-money valuation. That's 11% dilution.

Why this valuation? Comparable seed rounds for healthcare SaaS with traction are $5-8M. We have validated product, founder-market fit, and customer pipeline.

Use of funds: 50% hiring VP Sales and team. 35% operations, infrastructure, marketing. 15% runway buffer.

Milestones: March 31—50+ calls, 1-2 LOIs. June 30—3+ pilots deployed, $150K+ ARR. October—$300-500K ARR, Series A conversations. December—$500K-$1M ARR, Series A close."

**Slide 10 (Vision) - 2 min:**
"Long-term, we're building the intelligence layer for healthcare quality. Every care coordinator uses our system. Every provider sees smart narratives. Every executive sees financial impact.

Year 1 is about proving product-market fit with health plans. Year 2 is scaling to health systems and ACOs. Year 3 is market leadership.

For investors, the exit is clear. 5-7 year timeline, 10-15x revenue multiple, $500M-$1B acquisition price. That's 50-100x return on seed capital if we execute.

We have the product, the market validation, and the execution plan. We just need capital to scale the team. Let's build this."

